13 SECTION 1.2.(a) The amendments set out in Section 1.1 of this act shall be
14 submitted to the qualified voters of the State at the statewide general election to be held in
15 November 2026, which election shall be conducted under the laws then governing elections in
16 the State. Ballots, voting systems, or both may be used in accordance with Chapter 163 of the
17 General Statutes. The question to be used in the voting systems and ballots shall be:
18 "[ ] FOR [ ] AGAINST
19 A constitutional amendment providing for a nonpartisan process to be established in
20 law to redistrict the State for the purpose of electing members of the General Assembly and the
21 United States House of Representatives. The General Assembly would establish the nonpartisan
22 process in law and have no other role in the creation of the districts."
23 SECTION 1.2.(b) If a majority of votes cast on the question are in favor of the
24 amendments set out in Section 1.1 of this act, the State Board of Elections shall certify the
25 amendments to the Secretary of State. The Secretary of State shall enroll the amendments so
26 certified among the permanent records of that office. The amendments are effective upon
27 certification.
28 SECTION 1.3. Except as otherwise provided, this Part is effective when it becomes
29 law.
