1 candidate filing shall be as provided by G.S. 163-358 without designation as
2 to the vacancy.
3 (3) The general election ballot shall contain, without designation as to vacancy,
4 spaces for the election to fill the vacancy where nominations were made or
5 candidates filed under subdivision (1) or (2) of this section. Except as provided
6 in G.S. 163-358, the persons receiving the highest numbers of votes equal to
