1 PART IV. ONLINE VOTER REGISTRATION
2 SECTION 4.1. G.S. 163-82.3(a) reads as rewritten:
3 "(a) Form Developed by State Board of Elections. – The State Board of Elections shall
4 develop an application form for voter registration. registration that may be (i) printed out in blank
5 form or (ii) filled in online as set forth in G.S. 163-82.5A. Any person may use the form to apply
6 to do any of the following:
7 (1) Register to vote.
8 (2) Change party affiliation or unaffiliated status.
9 (3) Report a change of address within a county.
10 (4) Report a change of name.
11 The county board of elections for the county where the applicant resides shall accept the form
12 as application for any of those purposes if the form is submitted as set out in G.S. 163-82.3.this
13 section."
14 SECTION 4.2. Article 7A of Chapter 163 of the General Statutes is amended by
15 adding a new section to read:
16 "§ 163-82.5A. Online voter registration.
17 (a) This section may be cited as the "Online Voter Registration Act."
18 (b) Require Availability of Internet for Voter Registration. – The State Board of Elections
19 shall ensure that the following services are available to the public at any time on its official public
20 website:
21 (1) Online application for voter registration, the content of which shall be
22 equivalent to the form provided by designated voter registration agencies.
23 (2) Online assistance to those applying to register to vote.
24 (3) Online completion and submission by applicants of the voter registration
25 application, including the signature of the applicant pursuant to subsection (d)
26 of this section.
27 (4) Online receipt of completed voter registration applications.
28 (c) To the extent any State agency described in G.S. 163-82.19 or G.S. 163-82.20 has
29 signatures of clients, those agencies shall cooperate in sharing those signatures with the State
30 Board of Elections.
31 (d) An application submitted under this section shall be deemed submitted to the election
32 authority on the date it is received.
33 (e) An applicant for voter registration under this section provides a signature by doing
34 any of the following:
35 (1) In the case of an applicant who has a signature on file with a State government
36 agency, authorizing the agency to transmit that signature to election officials.
37 (2) Submitting with the application an electronic copy of the applicant's
38 handwritten signature through electronic means in a manner prescribed by the
39 State Board of Elections.
40 (f) Upon submission of a completed voter registration application under this section, the
41 State Board of Elections official website shall generate an immediate electronic confirmation on
42 the website that the application has been received, with instructions as to how the applicant may
43 check the status of the application thereafter.
44 (g) The State Board of Elections shall accept an online voter registration application
45 submitted under this section and ensure that the individual is registered to vote in this State if
46 each of the following is satisfied:
47 (1) The individual meets the same voter registration eligibility requirements
48 applicable to individuals who register to vote by mail.
49 (2) The individual provides a signature in accordance with subsection (e) of this
50 section.
Page 16 DRH10316-LUxfaye-53B

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (h) The State Board of Elections shall inform the applicant for voter registration of the
2 disposition of the application by regular mail. Additionally, the State Board shall make available
3 to the applicant the option to receive the disposition notification by email.
4 (i) No legal distinction shall be made between registration under this section and
5 registration by written application in accordance with the provisions of this Article.
6 (j) The State Board of Elections shall ensure that any registered voter may at any time
7 update the voter's registration information, including the voter's address, online through the State
8 Board's official public website in accordance with maintenance of the computerized statewide
9 voter registration list.
10 (k) Except as provided in G.S. 163-82.6A, the State Board shall revise any information
11 on the computerized list to reflect the update made by the voter at any time until the deadlines
12 for registration under G.S. 163-82.6(d) for a primary or general election.
13 (l) Upon receipt of updated registration information under this section, the State Board
14 of Elections shall send a notice confirming receipt of the updated information by regular mail,
15 and by email, if available."
